    <AbstractNarration>The focus of this work is (1) on principles and applications of manipulating gaseous Bose-Einstein Condensate (BEC's) with laser light under realistic experimental conditions. The research will also focus (2) on modeling the loading of optical lattices using a BEC and (3) on studying the characteristics of a practical atom laser beam. The work will provide new capabilities for the investigation of practical atom lasers.</AbstractNarration>
